        section#descricao.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center
                    h1 Local Administration

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead.fw-bold The Master's degree in Municipal Administration is awarded to students who demonstrate the ability to:
                    p.lead a) develop and deepen the knowledge acquired at the level of the 1st cycle, in order to achieve original developments and applications, in many cases in a research context;
                    p.lead b) apply their knowledge and their ability to understand and solve problems in new and unfamiliar situations, in broad and multidisciplinary contexts, even if related to their area of study;
                    p.lead c) integrate knowledge, deal with complex issues, develop solutions or make judgments in situations of limited or incomplete information, including reflections on the ethical and social implications and responsibilities that result from or condition these solutions and judgments;
                    p.lead d) communicate its conclusions, and the knowledge and reasoning behind them, to both experts and non-specialists, in a clear and unambiguous manner;
                    p.lead e) develop skills that enable them to learn lifelong in a fundamentally self-directed or autonomous way.

        section#perfil.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Profile of the study program

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead The master's degree in Municipal Administration aims to create assets with the ability to interact with local governance issues.
                    p.lead The concentration of responsibilities in the production of public goods and services at the local level, the increase in complexity and the demand for increased efficiency in urban governance, requires human resources capable of promoting efficient solutions duly conformed to the law and promoting an urban regime of cooperation between sectors of society.

        section#diplomados.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Occupational profile of graduates

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead The master's course aims to provide students with training that allows them to work in Public Administration, particularly within the scope of municipal governance, in the sphere of the local business sector, as well as to promote academic training for professionals who, in the exercise of their public and private functions, need to interact with the public and private sphere. In addition to the national orientation, the master's course aims to capture and respond to a very specific regional audience, fundamental in view of the new existing organics and inherent organic functionalities.

